A 21-year-old man drowned in a swimming pool on Robben Island in Cape Town on Monday, the National Sea Rescue Institute (NSRI) said.According to NSRI, the man had been removed from the swimming pool and a nursing sister on the island had initiated Cardio Pulmonary Resuscitation (CPR) efforts.The incident occurred when the Philippi resident was visiting family who work on the island.&#8220;On arrival at Murray s Harbour NSRI medics were transported to the swimming pool by Robben Island staff and the EMS/AMS Skymed helicopter arrived on the scene but the man was found to be deceased, suspected to be from a fatal drowning accident.&#8220;Police are arranging to take the body into the care of the Forensic Pathology Services and Police have opened an inquest docket,&#8221; said NSRI.The institute has conveyed sincere condolences to the family and friends of the deceased man.-TNA Reporter